2.00	Chopin_Piano_Competition	International Chopin Piano Competition	The International Chopin Piano Competition (Polish: Międzynarodowy Konkurs Pianistyczny im. Fryderyka Chopina), often referred to as the Chopin Competition, is a piano competition held in Warsaw, Poland to honour the name of Frédéric Chopin. It is one of the oldest and most prestigious music competitions in the world. It was initiated in 1927 and has been held every five years since 1955. It is one of few competitions devoted entirely to the works of a single composer.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/36/Chopin_Intl_Piano_Competition_2005.jpg/250px-Chopin_Intl_Piano_Competition_2005.jpg
